<DOC><DOCNO> AP891211-0085 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-11-89 1217EST</FILEID><FIRST>u a PM-WeatherpageWeather 1stLd-Writethru a0489 12-11 0666</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0489,0678</SECOND><HEAD>Snow Over Midwest; Storm Hits Utah, Colorado Mountains</HEAD><HEAD>Eds: Leads with 9 grafs to UPDATE with pile-up in Colorado, frigidwind-chills in North Dakota, and update number of dead in North Carolinato eight, sted seven. Picks up 10th graf pvs, `The entire...'.</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Snow and low temperatures combined to make the Rockies' roadsslick early today, causing numerous road pile-ups. Elsewhere, snowfell in much of the Midwest, and wind-chills far below zero numbedparts of the Dakotas.   A winter storm warning was posted for locally heavy snow alongwith gusty winds and low temperatures in a portion of Coloradoincluding the southern foothills and the Sangre de Cristo mountains.   In northern Utah, slippery roads were blamed for accidentsinvolving more than 20 cars near Salt Lake International Airport onSunday night. Numerous minor injuries were reported.   Most of Colorado east of the Continental Divide was hard hit bythe storm, which left a slew of motor vehicle accidents in its wakeSunday, including a 20-car pileup on Interstate 25 near Johnstownthat closed the highway for two hours. Three people suffered minorinjuries in that accident.   Much of the country's northern tier, the northern Rockies andIowa and Nebraska registered temperatures in the single digits thismorning. Wind chills as low as 50 degrees below zero were reportedin North Dakota.   Snow was reported early today from Denver to Albany, N.Y. Citiesblanketed with snow included St. Louis, Cleveland, Detroit, Chicagoand North Platte, Neb.   The cold reached down into the panhandle of Texas, where snowwas possible today. A winter storm watch for snow and freezing rainalso was forecast for tonight and Tuesday over northern Mississippi.   Out West, high winds were expected today across SouthernCalifornia, where gusts up to 70 mph were possible in the mountains.   In North Carolina, the first wintry storm of the season wasblamed for the deaths of eight motorists. The storm knocked outpower to thousands of households and toppled two television towersbefore moving out to sea Sunday.   Towers for WPTF-TV and WRAL-TV, both Raleigh stations, collapsedSunday within a half-hour of each other, spokesmen for the stationssaid. The towers stand side-by-side in Auburn just south of Raleigh.   The entire nation, however, wasn't under a wintry grip.   In El Paso, Texas, the temperature reached 73 degrees Sunday,breaking the record for the date. The nation's high Sunday was 83degrees at San Angelo, Texas.   Other reports at 4 a.m. EST today:   _EAST: Albany, N.Y., 29 snow; Atlanta 39 cloudy; Boston 32cloudy; Buffalo 27; Charleston, S.C., 41 cloudy; Chattanooga 35partly cloudy; Cincinnati 32 foggy; Cleveland 29 snow; Detroit 26snow; Hatteras 31 fair; Jacksonville 34 foggy; Key West 63 partlycloudy; Knoxville 31 foggy; Macon 38 foggy; Miami 55 partly cloudy;New York 32 cloudy; Philadelphia 23 fair; Pittsburgh 26 foggy;Portland, Maine, 17 fair; Richmond 33 foggy; Tampa 42 fair;Washington, D.C. 26 foggy.   _CENTRAL: Bismarck 05 windy; Chicago 25 snow; Denver 13 snow;Des Moines 08 fair; Fort Worth 37; Indianapolis 31 snow; KansasCity 13 snow; Little Rock 43 fair; Louisville 33 foggy; Memphis 42cloudy; Nashville 40 cloudy; New Orleans 59 cloudy; North Platte 13snow; Oklahoma City 28 windy; Omaha 05 windy; Rapid City 00 windy;St. Louis 31 snow; Minneapolis-St. Paul 06 fair; Sault Ste. Marie03 fair; San Antonio 50 fair.   _WEST: Albuquerque 29 cloudy; Anchorage 30 partly cloudy; Boise21 fair; Casper 04 snow; Fairbanks 18 cloudy; Great Falls 16 fair;Honolulu 66 fair; Las Vegas 41 fair; Los Angeles 52 foggy; Medford29 foggy; Pendleton 27 fair; Phoenix 48 fair; Portland, Ore., 30partly cloudy; Reno 21 fair; Salt Lake City 20 fair; San Diego 54cloudy; San Francisco 53 fair; Seattle 37 foggy; Spokane 21 fair.   _INTERNATIONAL: Calgary 01 partly cloudy; Montreal 05 fair;Ottawa 07 fair; Regina 14 fair; Toronto 27 cloudy; Winnipeg 17fair; Mexico City 48 fair; Acapulco 75 fair.</TEXT></DOC>